[[File:Chorsu.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Chorsu in [[Samarkand]], [[Uzbekistan]]]]
'''Chorsu''' ({{lang-uz|Chorsu}} and {{lang-ru|<U+0427><U+043E><U+0440><U+0441><U+0443>}}) in [[Samarkand]], [[Uzbekistan]], is an old domed [[bazaar]] building, constructed in the 15th century, rebuilt in the 18th century.  It is located near [[Registan#Chorsu|the Registan]], on its northeast side. <ref> [http://www.samarkand-hotels.com/samarkand/sights/chorsu-samarkand.htm Ancient Business Center "Chorsu" in Samarkand] </ref>

The main bazaar has already moved to [[Siyob Bazaar]] near [[Bibi-Khanym Mosque]]. Chorsu has recently been converted into an art gallery. "Chorsu" is a word from the [[Persian language]], meaning a "crossroad". <ref> 
[http://www.silkroadadventures.net/en/Uzbekistan/17Cities/17Cities-15.html Chorsu market in Samarkand] </ref>

